l%20line]\nis_a: UBERON:0006800 ! anatomical line\nrelationship: connects UBERON:0000209 ! tetrapod frontal bone\nrelationship: connects UBERON:0000210 ! tetrapod parietal bone\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8415-4848 ! Helena Machado\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8500001\nname: euryon\ndef: \"An anatomical point on the most lateral point of the neurocranium.\" [ISBN:9780873659505]\nis_a: UBERON:0006983 ! anatomical point\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8415-4848 ! Helena Machado\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001703 ! neurocranium\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8500002\nname: supraorbital foramen\ndef: \"A bony elongated opening located above the orbit and under the forehead.\" [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supraorbital_foramen]\nis_a: UBERON:0005744 ! bone foramen\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8415-4848 ! Helena Machado\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000209 ! tetrapod frontal bone\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8500003\nname: supraorbitale\ndef: \"An anatomical point on the median point of the line joining the aboral borders of the supraorbital foramen.\" [ISBN:9780873659505]\nis_a: UBERON:0006983 ! anatomical point\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8415-4848 ! Helena Machado\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8500002 ! supraorbital foramen\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8500004\nname: entorbitale\ndef: \"An anatomical point on the naso-medial indentation of the orbit that corresponds with the inner angle of the eye in the living animal.\" [ISBN:9780873659505]\nis_a: UBERON:0006983 ! anatomical point\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8415-4848 ! Helena Machado\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001697 ! orbit of skull\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600000\nname: lobular bronchiole\ndef: \"A conductive airway that branches into terminal bronchioles.\" [PMID:16543587, PMID:27611890]\nsynonym: \"preterminal bronchiole\" EXACT [PMID:16543587]\nis_a: UBERON:0002186 ! bronchiole\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-08T13:31:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600001\nname: epithelium of lobular bronchiole\ndef: \"An epithelium of the lobular bronchiole.\" [FMA:62497]\nsynonym: \"epithelium of preterminal bronchiole\" EXACT [PMID:16543587]\nsynonym: \"lobular bronchiole epithelium\" EXACT [FMA:62497]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000483 ! epithelium\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600000 ! lobular bronchiole\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-10T14:26:09Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600002\nname: mucosa of lobular bronchiole\ndef: \"A mucosa that is part of a lobular bronchiole.\" [FMA:263230]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000344 ! mucosa\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600000 ! lobular bronchiole\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-10T14:48:35Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600003\nname: smooth muscle tissue of lobular bronchiole\ndef: \"A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a lobular bronchiole.\" [FMA:261081]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001135 ! smooth muscle tissue\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600000 ! lobular bronchiole\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-10T14:54:06Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600004\nname: visceral muscle tissue\ndef: \"A muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).\" [BTO:0002780, CLAO:0001295]\ncomment: It is quite common to refer to visceral muscles as smooth muscles, by analogy with vertebrates; however, most visceral muscles in arthropods are actually striated. {xref=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smooth_muscle\", xref=\"FBbt:00005070\", comment=\"PMID:8720463\"}\nsynonym: \"visceral muscle\" EXACT [] {comment=\"BTO:0002780\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0002385 ! muscle tissue\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0008007 ! visceral muscle cell\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-16T10:17:46Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600005\nname: visceral smooth muscle tissue\ndef: \"A smooth muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).\" [PMID:12132390, PMID:33729000]\nsynonym: \"smooth musculature of viscera\" EXACT [PMID:12132390]\nsynonym: \"visceral smooth muscle\" EXACT [PMID:12132390]\nis_a: UBERON:0001135 ! smooth muscle tissue\nis_a: UBERON:8600004 ! visceral muscle tissue\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-16T10:32:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600006\nname: visceral striated muscle tissue\ndef: \"A striated muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).\" [https://pressbooks.pub/rbtallitsch/chapter/chapter-6-muscle-tissue/, PMID:8720463]\nsynonym: \"striated visceral muscle tissue\" EXACT []\nis_a: UBERON:0002036 ! striated muscle tissue\nis_a: UBERON:8600004 ! visceral muscle tissue\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-16T10:34:43Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600007\nname: visceral transversely striated muscle tissue\ndef: \"A striated visceral muscle tissue that has a transverse striation.\" [PMID:8720463]\nsynonym: \"transversely striated visceral muscle tissue\" EXACT []\nis_a: UBERON:8600006 ! visceral striated muscle tissue\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-16T10:54:01Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600008\nname: visceral obliquely striated muscle tissue\ndef: \"A striated visceral muscle tissue that has an oblique striation.\" [PMID:8720463, PMID:872199]\nis_a: UBERON:8600006 ! visceral striated muscle tissue\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-21T09:26:41Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600009\nname: subsegmental bronchus\ndef: \"Branch of conducting airway between a segmental bronchus and a preterminal bronchiole.\" [ISBN:0781785898, ISBN:9780702077050, Wikipedia:Bronchus]\ncomment: Like other bronchi, the walls of a subsegmental bronchus contain plates of cartilage. Notably, the cartilage plates become smaller and more widely dispersed with each branching. {xref=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-12-381361-9.00009-3\", xref=\"PMID:14913504\"}\nsynonym: \"intrasegmental bronchus\" RELATED [https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-12-381361-9.00009-3]\nis_a: UBERON:0002185 ! bronchus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9185-3994 ! Gloria S Pryhuber\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:0001956 ! cartilage of bronchus\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:0004242 ! bronchus smooth muscle\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:0004883 ! lung mesenchyme\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:8410043 ! bronchus submucosal gland\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000101 ! lobe of lung\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600017 ! bronchopulmonary segment\nrelationship: proximally_connected_to UBERON:0002184 ! segmental bronchus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-03-14T14:54:15Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600010\nname: bronchial submucosal gland ciliated duct\ndef: \"A ciliated duct part of a bronchial submucosal gland.\" [PMID:30864819]\nintersection_of: UBERON:8600014 ! submucosal gland ciliated duct\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8410043 ! bronchus submucosal gland\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9185-3994 ! Gloria S Pryhuber\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-02T08:07:56Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600011\nname: tracheal submucosal gland ciliated duct\ndef: \"A ciliated duct part of a tracheal submucosal gland.\" [PMID:30864819]\nintersection_of: UBERON:8600014 ! submucosal gland ciliated duct\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0005203 ! trachea gland\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9185-3994 ! Gloria S Pryhuber\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-02T08:08:14Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600012\nname: submucosal gland acinus\ndef: \"A spherical or tubular structure in a submucosal gland that produces and secretes mucus and other substances into the ducts leading to the surface epithelium.\" [PMID:17394068, PMID:17707699, PMID:25648514, PMID:30864819]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0009842 ! glandular acinus\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0011148 ! submucosal gland\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-02T08:57:27Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600013\nname: submucosal gland collecting duct\ndef: \"A non-secretory tubular structure in the submucosal gland where secretions are collected before flowing towards the surface epithelium.\" [PMID:10520827, PMID:17707699, PMID:25648514, PMID:30864819]\nis_a: UBERON:0000058 ! duct\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0011148 ! submucosal gland\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-02T08:08:59Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600014\nname: submucosal gland ciliated duct\ndef: \"A ciliated tubular structure in a submucosal gland connecting the submucosal gland collecting duct with the surface epithelium.\" [PMID:17707699, PMID:30864819]\nis_a: UBERON:0000058 ! duct\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: has_part CL:0000067 ! ciliated epithelial cell\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0011148 ! submucosal gland\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-02T08:09:14Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600015\nname: posterior sector of right lobe of liver\ndef: \"The posterior sector of the right lobe of the liver.\" [PMID:30992874]\nsynonym: \"lateral sector of right lobe of liver\" EXACT [PMID:24453062]\nsynonym: \"liver right lateral lobe\" RELATED [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6443-9376]\nsynonym: \"right hepatic posterior sector\" EXACT [PMID:30487943]\nis_a: UBERON:0001062 ! anatomical entity\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6443-9376 ! Jennifer R. Smith\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001114 ! right lobe of liver\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-15T10:46:34Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600016\nname: anterior sector of right lobe of liver\ndef: \"The anterior sector of the right lobe of the liver.\" [PMID:30992874]\nsynonym: \"liver right medial lobe\" RELATED [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6443-9376]\nsynonym: \"medial sector of right lobe of liver\" EXACT [PMID:24453062]\nsynonym: \"right hepatic anterior sector\" EXACT [PMID:30487943]\nis_a: UBERON:0001062 ! anatomical entity\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001114 ! right lobe of liver\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-05-15T10:52:39Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600017\nname: bronchopulmonary segment\ndef: \"A discrete anatomical unit of the lung that is composed of a segmental bronchus and the lung tissue supplied by that bronchus. A bronchopulmonary segment exhibits a pyramidal shape, with its apex pointing towards the center of the lung and its base toward the pleural surface.\" [doi:10.1016/j.mpaic.2008.09.022, FMA:7312, PMID:18271171, PMID:33620799]\ncomment: A bronchopulmonary segment is surrounded by connective tissue septa, which are continuous with the pleural surface and prevent air collateralization between segments somewhat. In humans, the right lung has ten bronchopulmonary segments and eight or nine bronchopulmonary segments in the left lung. {xref=\"doi:10.1016/j.mpaic.2008.09.022\", xref=\"PMID:18271171\"}\nsynonym: \"lung segment\" EXACT [PMID:33620799]\nis_a: UBERON:0000063 ! organ subunit\nrelationship: contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0000101 ! lobe of lung\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9185-3994 ! Gloria S Pryhuber\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000101 ! lobe of lung\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-07-20T12:43:29Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600018\nname: neuroendocrine system\ndef: \"A regulatory system of the body that integrates the nervous system and the endocrine system. This system is formed by specialized neuroendocrine cells located mainly in the nervous system and neuroendocrine glands. However, they can also be found as either single cells or small clusters of cells dispersed throughout the surface epithelium of different tissues. The neuroendocrine system functions through the release of neurotransmitters and neurohormones, enabling communication between the endocrine and nervous systems to govern vitally important processes that include growth, reproduction, metabolism and energy homeostasis, electrolyte and water balance, and responses to stress.\" [doi:10.1016/B978-0-12-375097-6.10001-0, PMID:15481802, PMID:17003257, PMID:25905254, Wikipedia:endocrinology]\ncomment: In vertebrates, the hypothalamic-pituitary-target organ axis (H-P axis), the autonomic nervous system (ANS) and the diffuse neuroendocrine or APUD system contribute to the neuroendocrine system. {xref=\"PMID:15481802\"}\nsynonym: \"NES\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:15481802]\nis_a: UBERON:0000467 ! anatomical system\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:0000949 ! endocrine system\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:0001016 ! nervous system\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-08-29T10:49:45Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600019\nname: placental basal plate\ndef: \"A maternal facing structure of the placental disc, adjacent to the intervillous space. Major components of the placental basal plate include decidua basalis, fibrinoid, connective tissue, extravillous trophoblasts, and residues of degenerating villi and maternal vessels.\" [PMID:17059842, PMID:32108320]\nsynonym: \"PBP\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:31002314]\nsynonym: \"placenta basal plate\" EXACT [PMID:32108320]\nis_a: UBERON:0010000 ! multicellular anatomical structure\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600038 ! placental disc\nrelationship: present_in_taxon NCBITaxon:9443 {xref=\"PMID:31002314\"} ! Primates\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-09-14T08:19:13Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600020\nname: placental septum\ndef: \"An extension of the basal plate that protrudes into the intervillous space, creating a system of grooves which delimit elevated areas, also known as cotyledons or maternal lobes.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:32108320]\nsynonym: \"placenta septum\" EXACT [PMID:35190336]\nsynonym: \"placental septa\" RELATED OMO:0003004 [doi:10.1007/BF00406305]\nis_a: UBERON:0003037 ! septum\nrelationship: adjacent_to UBERON:0010008 ! placental cotyledon\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600019 ! placental basal plate\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-09-14T08:59:34Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600021\nname: chorionic plate blood vessel\ndef: \"A blood vessel that is part of the chorionic plate.\" [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK53254/]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001981 ! blood vessel\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0004027 ! chorionic plate\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-09-14T09:09:36Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600022\nname: pulmonary interlobular septum\ndef: \"A septum that surrounds and gives shape to the secondary pulmonary lobules, it is composed of connective tissue within which run the pulmonary veins and lymphatic vessels.\" [doi:10.53347/rID-8764, PMID:22283705, PMID:3259815]\nsynonym: \"interlobular interstitium\" RELATED [doi:10.53347/rID-8764]\nsynonym: \"interlobular septa\" BROAD OMO:0003004 [PMID:3259815]\nsynonym: \"interlobular septum\" BROAD [doi:10.53347/rID-8764]\nis_a: UBERON:0000114 ! lung connective tissue\nis_a: UBERON:0003037 ! septum\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:0002016 ! pulmonary vein\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:0018227 ! pulmonary lymphatic vessel\nrelationship: surrounds UBERON:0010369 ! secondary pulmonary lobule\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-10-23T08:52:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600023\nname: placental villous stroma\ndef: \"A stroma that is part of a chorionic villus (placental villus). A placental villous stroma supports the fetal capillaries and villous trophoblast.\" [PMID:31512233]\nsynonym: \"chorionic villous stroma\" EXACT [PMID:12624135]\nsynonym: \"CVS\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:12624135]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0003891 ! stroma\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-07-04T10:46:17Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600024\nname: pulmonary venule\ndef: \"A venule that is part of a lung and drains oxygenated blood from pulmonary capillaries. A pulmonary venule merges into a pulmonary vein branch that runs in the pulmonary interlobular septa.\" [PMID:22283705, PMID:30247823]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001979 ! venule\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002048 ! lung\nrelationship: connected_to UBERON:0002016 ! pulmonary vein\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0013127 ! pulmonary venous system\nrelationship: vessel_drains_blood_from UBERON:0016405 ! pulmonary capillary\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-10-24T11:26:27Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600025\nname: intervillous space\ndef: \"An anatomical space that separates the basal plate and the chorionic plate. The intervillous space is filled with endometrial gland secretions during early stages of the pregnancy and later perfused with maternal blood, bathing the chorionic villous tree.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:32108320]\nis_a: UBERON:0000464 ! anatomical space\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600038 ! placental disc\nrelationship: surrounds UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T11:50:32Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600026\nname: chorionic villous tree\ndef: \"A tree-like structure formed by chorionic villi that sprouts from the chorionic plate in the placental disc. The arborous shape of the chorionic villous tree provides maximal contact area with maternal blood in the intervillous space.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"placental villous tree\" EXACT [PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"villous tree\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600038 ! placental disc\nrelationship: proximally_connected_to UBERON:0004027 ! chorionic plate\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T11:57:24Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600027\nname: chorionic stem villus\ndef: \"A chorionic villus that provides structural support to the villous tree. A chorionic stem villus is characterized by a condensed fibrous stroma in which fetal arteries, veins, arterioles, and venules are embedded. It represents a distributing framework for fetal chorionic circulation, supplying the floating villi. It can exhibit a diameter ranging from approximately 3000 μm (trunci near the chorionic plate) to 80 μm (smallest ramuli chorii).\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"placental stem villus\" EXACT [PMID:9260835]\nis_a: UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:8600029 ! chorionic immature intermediate villus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:00:59Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600028\nname: chorionic mesenchymal villus\ndef: \"The first generation of a tertiary villus that is derived from a syncytial sprout by the invasion of the mesenchyme, in which blood vessels differentiate through vasculogenesis, and gradually transforms into a new immature intermediate villus. A chorionic mesenchymal villus has a thick trophoblastic covering, and cytotrophoblast cells are interposed between syncytium and the trophoblastic basal lamina over 50–100% of the surface. The stroma is characterized by loosely arranged collagen fibers that enmesh mesenchymal and some villous macrophages. The fetal capillaries are poorly developed.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"mesenchymal villus\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0009995 ! tertiary chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:38:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600029\nname: chorionic immature intermediate villus\ndef: \"A bulbous, immature chorionic villus that is formed of loose connective tissue with few fetal vessels. A chorionic immature intermediate villus develops from a chorionic mesenchymal villus, and is the forerunner of a chorionic stem villus.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:487407, PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"immature intermediate villus\" RELATED [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:21452443]\nis_a: UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:8600028 ! chorionic mesenchymal villus\nrelationship: develops_into UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:41:05Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600030\nname: chorionic terminal villus\ndef: \"The most distal part of a chorionic villus. A chorionic terminal villus is a grape-like structure characterized by a high degree of capillarization and highly dilated sinusoids. A terminal villus has less stroma and a discontinuous cytotrophoblast layer, and contains 4–6 fetal capillaries per cross section. It exhibits a diameter ranging from 40 to about 80 μm.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:21452443]\nsynonym: \"terminal villus\" BROAD [PMID:21452443]\nis_a: UBERON:8600032 ! chorionic floating villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:41:16Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600031\nname: chorionic mature intermediate villus\ndef: \"A slender branch of a chorionic stem villus. A chorionic mature intermediate villus lacks fetal arterioles and venules in the stroma, which is composed of slender fetal capillaries embedded into a loose connective tissue that is rich in cells but poor in fibers. It exhibits a diameter ranging from 60 to about 100 μm.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:21452443]\nsynonym: \"mature intermediate villus\" BROAD [PMID:21452443]\nis_a: UBERON:8600032 ! chorionic floating villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: proximally_connected_to UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:41:28Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600032\nname: chorionic floating villus\ndef: \"A chorionic villus that is not attached to the placental basal plate and it is immersed in maternal blood.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:31870762, PMID:32513715]\nsynonym: \"floating villus\" BROAD [PMID:31870762]\nsynonym: \"free-floating villus\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:42:09Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600033\nname: chorionic anchoring villus\ndef: \"A distal smaller chorionic stem villus that is connected to the maternal side of the placenta (in early gestational stages to the decidua, and later to the developing basal plate) via a cytotrophoblast cell column. A chorionic anchoring villus stabilizes the position of the villous tree in the maternal intervillous bloodstream.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:15142834, PMID:32513715, PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"anchoring villus\" BROAD [PMID:15142834]\nis_a: UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:42:20Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600034\nname: jejunum lamina propria\ndef: \"A lamina propria that is part of a jejunum.\" [PMID:9394954]\nsynonym: \"jejunal lamina propria\" EXACT [PMID:1556433]\nsynonym: \"lamina propria of jejunum\" EXACT [PMID:22763879]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000030 ! lamina propria\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002115 ! jejunum\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8134-3037\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0008343 ! intestinal villus of jejunum\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-09T16:36:35Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600035\nname: ileum lamina propria\ndef: \"A lamina propria that is part of an ileum.\" [PMID:29316348]\nsynonym: \"ileal lamina propria\" EXACT [PMID:37467267]\nsynonym: \"lamina propria of ileum\" EXACT [PMID:36067905]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000030 ! lamina propria\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002116 ! ileum\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8134-3037\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0008344 ! intestinal villus of ileum\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-09T16:48:17Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600036\nname: kidney loop of Henle long descending thin limb outer medulla\ndef: \"A section of the long descending thin limb of the loop of Henle that is part of the outer medulla of the kidney.\" [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"DTL2\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"long descending limb of the loop of Henle in the outer medulla\" EXACT [PMID:33769951]\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001293 ! outer medulla of kidney\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0005100 ! long descending thin limb\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-15T13:28:03Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600037\nname: kidney loop of Henle long descending thin limb inner medulla\ndef: \"A section of the long descending thin limb of the loop of Henle that is part of the inner medulla of the kidney.\" [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"DTL3\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"long descending limb of the loop of Henle in the inner medulla\" EXACT [PMID:33769951]\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001294 ! inner medulla of kidney\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0005100 ! long descending thin limb\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-15T13:32:25Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600038\nname: placental disc\ndef: \"A disc-shaped structure that is part of the placenta. A placental disc supports fetal development through the exchange of nutrients between maternal and fetal bloodstreams. The placental disc is structured to keep the blood streams separate, while maximizing surface area for the transport of nutrients between them, to maintain an immunological barrier.\" [PMID:35496035]\nsynonym: \"placental disk\" EXACT [PMID:30133439]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001987 ! placenta\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T17:50:20Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600039\nname: chorionic villous mesenchyme\ndef: \"A mesenchyme that is part of a chorionic villus.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0003104 ! mesenchyme\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:13:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600040\nname: chorionic stem villous blood vessel\ndef: \"A blood vessel that is part of a chorionic stem villus.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"stem villous vessel\" BROAD [PMID:7547738]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001981 ! blood vessel\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:14:32Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600041\nname: chorionic terminal villous capillary\ndef: \"A capillary that is part of a chorionic terminal villus. This capillary is generally narrow, but displays sinusoidal dilations along its length, often at the points of acute bends. These dilations bring the capillary endothelium into close contact with the overlying syncytiotrophoblast to form a vasculosyncytial membrane.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"terminal villous capillary\" BROAD [PMID:22461195]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001982 ! capillary\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600030 ! chorionic terminal villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:16:47Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600042\nname: endometrial lymphatic vessel\ndef: \"A lymphatic vessel that is part of an endometrium.\" [PMID:23054374]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001473 ! lymphatic vessel\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001295 ! endometrium\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:18:36Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600043\nname: lateral wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"A wall of the urinary bladder that is situated on the sides or flanks.\" [PMID:30548115]\nxref: FMA:15905\nis_a: UBERON:0001256 ! wall of urinary bladder\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:09:51Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600044\nname: left lateral wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"A lateral wall of the urinary bladder that is located on the left side.\" [PMID:30548115]\nsynonym: \"left wall of bladder\" BROAD [PMID:32233638]\nsynonym: \"left wall of urinary bladder\" EXACT [FMA:15907]\nxref: FMA:15907\nis_a: UBERON:8600043 ! lateral wall of urinary bladder\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:12:59Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600045\nname: right lateral wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"A lateral wall of the urinary bladder that is located on the right side.\" [PMID:30548115]\nsynonym: \"right wall of bladder\" BROAD [PMID:32233638]\nsynonym: \"right wall of urinary bladder\" EXACT [FMA:15906]\nxref: FMA:15906\nis_a: UBERON:8600043 ! lateral wall of urinary bladder\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:14:47Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600046\nname: anterior wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"The most anterior wall of the urinary bladder.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-642-71368-2_6, PMID:30548115]\nsynonym: \"anterior wall of bladder\" BROAD [PMID:30548115]\nsynonym: \"bladder roof\" RELATED [doi:10.1007/978-3-642-71368-2_6]\nxref: FMA:15903\nis_a: UBERON:0001256 ! wall of urinary bladder\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:20:11Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600047\nname: posterior wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"The most posterior wall of the urinary bladder.\" [PMID:30548115]\nsynonym: \"fundus\" RELATED [doi:10.1007/978-3-642-71368-2_6]\nsynonym: \"posterior wall of bladder\" BROAD [PMID:30548115]\nxref: FMA:15904\nis_a: UBERON:0001256 ! wall of urinary bladder\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:22:52Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600048\nname: apex of urinary bladder\ndef: \"The anterior angle of the superior surface of the urinary bladder. The apex of urinary bladder is connected to the umbilicus by the urachus in embryos, and by the median umbilical ligament, a remnant of urachus, in adults.\" [doi:10.1016/j.mpsur.2013.04.013, doi:10.1016/j.mpsur.2016.04.001, PMID:31372192]\nsynonym: \"apex of bladder\" BROAD [FMA:15914]\nsynonym: \"vertex of urinary bladder\" EXACT [PMID:35986765]\nxref: FMA:15914\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\nrelationship: connected_to UBERON:0007118 ! umbilicus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001255 ! urinary bladder\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:29:33Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600049\nname: dome of urinary bladder\ndef: \"The anterosuperior surface of the urinary bladder, with boundaries at the apex and fundus of the urinary bladder.\" [doi:10.1016/j.mpsur.2016.04.001]\nxref: FMA:265241\nis_a: UBERON:0006984 ! anatomical surface\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001255 ! urinary bladder\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:39:28Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600050\nname: trophoblast island\ndef: \"An accumulation of extravillous trophoblast cells at the tip of a floating villus or occasionally attached to the chorionic plate embedded in fibrin.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\ncomment: A trophoblast island is directly continuous with villous cytotrophoblast in places where the villous syncytiotrophoblast is interrupted. {xref=\"doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8\"}\nsynonym: \"cell island\" RELATED [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"intraplacental trophoblast island\" EXACT [PMID:33218578]\nsynonym: \"trophoblastic cell island\" EXACT [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000351 ! trophoblast cell\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: located_in UBERON:8600025 ! intervillous space\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-04-15T10:05:35Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600108\nname: proximal ureter\ndef: \"A segment of the ureter that extends from the renal pelvis to the common iliac artery bifurcation (to form the internal and external iliac arteries).\" [PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"abdominal ureter\" EXACT [PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"upper ureter\" EXACT [PMID:30422575]\nxref: FMA:15882\nis_a: UBERON:0006555 ! excretory tube\nrelationship: continuous_with UBERON:8600109 ! distal ureter\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000056 ! ureter\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-08-28T13:51:59Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600109\nname: distal ureter\ndef: \"A segment of the ureter that extends from the common iliac artery bifurcation to the bladder. From there, the ureter curves back and follows the lateral pelvic wall inferiorly to connect with the posterolateral bladder wall.\" [PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"lower ureter\" EXACT [PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"pelvic ureter\" EXACT [PMID:30422575]\nxref: FMA:15883\nis_a: UBERON:0006555 ! excretory tube\nrelationship: continuous_with UBERON:8600108 ! proximal ureter\nrelationship: continuous_with UBERON:8600110 ! intramural ureter\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000056 ! ureter\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-08-28T14:15:03Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600110\nname: intramural ureter\ndef: \"The terminal segment of the ureter that is continuous with the distal ureter, lies where the ureter enters the bladder and extends within the bladder wall. The intramural ureter is aperistaltic, serving as a reflux-preventing mechanism, preventing the backflow of urine from the bladder into the ureters.\" [PMID:14142154, PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"intravesical ureter\" EXACT [doi:10.53347/rID-23183, PMID:33085409]\nxref: FMA:77289\nis_a: UBERON:0006555 ! excretory tube\nrelationship: continuous_with UBERON:8600109 ! distal ureter\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000056 ! ureter\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-08-28T14:39:53Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600111\nname: right distal ureter\ndef: \"A distal ureter that is part of the right ureter.\" [PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"right lower ureter\" EXACT [PMID:30422575]\nsynonym: \"right pelvic ureter\" EXACT [PMID:30422575]\nxref: FMA:15886\nintersection_of: UBERON:8600109 ! distal ureter\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001222 ! right ureter\nrelationship: continuous_with UBERON:8600113 ! right proximal ureter\nrelationship: continuous_with UBERON:8600115 ! right intramural ureter\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-08-28T15:12:29Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600112\nname: left distal ureter\ndef: \"A distal uret